    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="607"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward to Mr. Ferry. </persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 83.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I thank you for your very interesting
                    confidential note of the 12th of March. It has been my earnest desire that Spain
                    might anticipate the other maritime powers in retiring from the erring policy of
                    1861. I feel sure that she would have done so if she could have ever so little
                    anticipated the events of the war during the present campaign. It is desirable
                    that you press the question upon the Spanish government now while the advantage
                    may even yet be secured. This proceeding in connexion with the restoration of
                    peace in Peru, and the retirement of Spain from Dominica, would probably open
                    harmonious and friendly relations between Spain and the United States for a
                    period as long as statesmen are accustomed to foresee events.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horatio Perry</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
